  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Safety Coordinator",
  "description": "<ul><li>Comply and assist in implementing the requirements of the WSH Act and all its subsidiary and statutory legal legislations.</li><li>Inspection of site daily and take appropriate corrective actions, prepares inspection report for project team to take an immediate action.</li><li>To investigate accidents / incidents / dangerous occurrences & put up reports & recommend remedial actions.</li><li>Conduct in-house safety orientation for all new joiners to the site, and also conduct daily tool box meeting.</li><li>Inspect project sites to ensure safety measures are being carried out at all times.</li><li>To conduct risk assessment and identify safety hazards on site</li><li>Work closely with WSHO and safety personnel to ensure safety are compliance</li><li>Any ad-hoc job assigned by superior</li><li>To participate in mass safety talk, tool box meeting and housekeeping.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>WSQ in Workplace Safety and Health.</li><li>WSQ Advance Certificate in Workplace Safety and Health.</li><li>Team oriented, attentive to details and organized.</li><li>A fast worker who is able to deliver under tight timelines.</li><li>Able to start work immediately or within short notice.</li></ul>",
